TITLE: Box Component with Ref in React
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use a Box component with a ref for direct DOM manipulation, including changing styles dynamically.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gluestack/gluestack-ui/blob/main/example/storybook/src/ui/components/Layout/Box/index.stories.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
function App () {
  const myRef = useRef({});
  useEffect(() => {
    const styleObj = {
      borderWidth: 2,
      borderRadius: 4,
      borderColor: '#1A91FF',
    };
  if(myRef.current && myRef.current.setNativeProps){
     myRef.current.setNativeProps({
      style: styleObj,
     });
    }
  }, [myRef]);
return (
  <Box 
  h={100}
  w={100}
  bg="$primary100"
  ref={myRef} />
);
}
```

