TITLE: Implementing Custom Font Resolution Strategy
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a custom font resolution strategy by providing a mapFonts function to the FontResolver constructor.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gluestack/gluestack-ui/blob/main/example/storybook/src/styled/plugins/FontsPlugin/index.stories.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
const CustomFontResolver = new FontResolver({
    mapFonts: (style) => {
      if (Platform.OS !== 'web') {
        style.fontFamily =
          style.fontFamily + '-' + style.fontWeight + '-' + style.fontStyle;
        style.fontWeight = undefined;
        style.fontStyle = undefined;
      }
    },
}),

export const config = {
  aliases: {},
  tokens: {},
  plugins: [CustomFontResolver],
};
```

